refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringarraynullpreg_replace_callback_array arraypattern stringarraysubject intlimit-1 intcount&null; intflags0
The behavior of this function is similar to preg_replace_callback, except that callbacks are executed on a per-pattern basis.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 preg_replace_callback_array returns an array if the
 subject parameter is an array, or a string
 otherwise. On errors the return value is &null;



 If matches are found, the new subject will be returned, otherwise
 subject will be returned unchanged.

  &reftitle.examples;



    preg_replace_callback_array example


<?php
$subject = 'Aaaaaa Bbb';

preg_replace_callback_array(
    [
        '~[a]+~i' => function ($match) {
            echo strlen($match[0]), ' matches for "a" found', PHP_EOL;
        },
        '~[b]+~i' => function ($match) {
            echo strlen($match[0]), ' matches for "b" found', PHP_EOL;
        }
    ],
    $subject
);
?>


    &example.outputs;


6 matches for "a" found
3 matches for "b" found
